This is safe because the `/user/:userId` route renders the same component. The old `/visitProfile?userId=...` route still works for any cached links or bookmarks.

### 3D. Add profile SEO meta tags

**File to create:** `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\seo\useProfileSeo.js`

Similar to `usePostSeo`, this hook updates meta tags when viewing a profile:

```javascript
const useProfileSeo = (userData) => {
    useEffect(() => {
        if (!userData?.name) return;

        const title = `${userData.name}'s Profile | ${SITE_NAME}`;
        const description = userData.bio 
            ? truncate(userData.bio, 160) 
            : `See ${userData.name}'s journals and opinions on ${SITE_NAME}`;

        document.title = title;
        updateMeta('seo-og-title', 'property', 'og:title', title);
        updateMeta('seo-og-description', 'property', 'og:description', description);

        // Person JSON-LD
